args: I've never heard of one of those.\nCan you make money off it?
Ah, yes. I forgot that you were raised\nby a traveling human and are not familiar\nwith the Vernal Banquet.
The Vernal Banquet is a festival held once\na year by sylvans who come together from\nall over the continent to celebrate spring.

The various villages each show off their
skills in competitions such as egg hunts
and archery contests, and winning them
is a source of great pride indeed.
Sooo NOT a way to make money.

Oh, there is money to be had for certain!
The Banquet has a market featuring local
foods and goods—it is a way for people to
promote their specialties with aplomb.
The people of my hometown used to work\ntogether to make loads of specialty goods\nfor this market!
Although it has been a while, so I cannot\nswear such is still the case.
Likewise. When I lost my hometown,\nthe Banquet ceased to mean as much.
Be that as it may, I imagine the\natmosphere at the Banquet would\nvery much be to a merchant's liking.
I'm fine! I was just thinking, it would be\ncool if I could help promote the Halidom...
Er, I mean... Never mind! I said nothing!\nLa de dum de dooo...
Yep! Whooole lotta nothing being said\nby this lady. Anyway, gotta fly!
...Do you think she's planning to\nparticipate in the Vernal Banquet?
It would not be a surprise—it IS a rather\nuniversal sylvan experience, after all.
In that case, maybe we should help her\nenjoy it. You know—as fellow long-ears.
A fine idea. In that case, let us go learn\nsome specialties of the Halidom before\nthe Banquet gets underway.
And so, the pair scoured the castle\nseeking out specialties of the Halidom...
I must say, I did not expect finding\nHalidom specialties to be so difficult.\nPerhaps we need to— Egads!

Heeey! If you're looking for the Halidom's
specialties, how about us? You won't
find this many dragons in one spot
anywhere else!

While I am grateful for the suggestion,
you are friends and colleagues of the
Halidom, not spectacles to be goggled
at.

Wait, we're friends? YAAAAAAAAY!
In that case, you can have some scales.
THOSE are a Halidom-exclusive item
for sure, right?
We will accept them with thanks.
If you guys are looking for Halidom\nspecialties, you've come to the right\nvegetable garden.
Lucky for you, it's harvest time!\nYou can have thiiis... And thiiis...\nOh, and a few of theeeese...
Please slow down, Aeleen!\nWe only have so many hands!

I can't help it! Everybody brought plants
from their own corners of the world, and
it would be wrong to leave any out.
...Oh, you HAVE to take this one here!
Let us try to confine ourselves to\nnon-sentient vegetables, mmm?
So you want Halidom specialties?\nIn that case...um...maybe...THESE!

Yes! Take this old book, as well as this
antique I found in the Halidom one day!
Oh, and don't forget the castle ITSELF is
an artifact of some value and significance!

Er, yes. As we are trying to sell these at
the market, we need things we can
actually carry. Also, are you sure you
want to part with these other items?
Hey, I've got an idea! How about this?!

Ta-daaaah! One Halidom knife! It's great
for a seasoned knife pro or a beginner
to the slashy arts. I'm fine parting with it
since it's not the legendary knife.
Wasn't this yours originally? Er, I mean,\nthis is wonderful. Thank you.
...And that is how we ended up with\nthis wide hodgepodge of items.

Vegetables, a knife, an old book,
a cake, tempered weapons, embroidered
clothes... Oh, and the autograph of a
certain vain king.
We also have a homemade makeup kit\nand a knitted ＂Luccy＂ doll—with still\nmore items on the way.
It is a ridiculous amount of items—and\nyet none of them really scream ＂this is\nthe Halidom's specialty＂ to me.

Saaaay, what are you two up to?
...Sakes alive, look at all the loot!
What the hey are you doing with
all this stuff?
Well, you mentioned wanting to show off\nthe Halidom's specialties earlier, so we\ngathered some up for you.
Yes. We thought it might be nice if you\ncould participate in the Banquet.
But while we have quite a wide variety\nof items, I fear we failed to find a true\nspecialty of the Halidom.
Oh, thank you both SO MUCH!\nI'm sure this will be enough to show\neveryone our Halidom pride!
Er, but which are you going to use?\nThere doesn't seem to be any rhyme\nor reason to this pile of items.
Which is GREAT! Now watch and learn...
We set up the stall just as you asked,\nbut is this really what you want?
Indeed, none of the other stalls seem to\nhave quite so...scattered a selection.
You're just gonna have to trust my ol'\nmerchant judgment. Speaking of which,\nhere come the customers now!
What am I gonna check out this year?\nAohri Village's mushroom pie?\nOr maybe Rustu Village's crafts!
...Huh? ＂The Halidom?＂ Where's that?\nI've never heard of it.
Excuse me, but could I take a\nlook at your—AAAAAH!
I've been looking for this book forever!\nAnd check out the craftsmanship on this...\nAugh! Augh! This scale! So shiny!
E-excuse me, madam! This thread is a\nspecialty of my village—might I trade it\nfor this dragon scale here?
Ah, you've quite the discerning eye, sir!\nVery well, that seems a fair trade.\nThank you for your custom!
*sniff* I know that scent! It's the newest\nmakeup collection from the famed\nbeautician, isn't it?!
Excuse me, but someone said this stall\nis selling a bunch of rare vegetables?
My stars and garters!\nThey just keep coming!

That's because we've got everything!
When a ton of different folks live together
under one roof, it means you have a ton
of unusual things to sell.
THIS is what I meant when I talked about\nshowing off the specialties of the Halidom.
Now come one, come all! We're packed\nto the gills with goods recommended by\nthe Halidom's many residents!
Whew! I think we've finally hit a lull.\nGoodness, but I am simply BEAT!
That's proof of a satisfying day, I'd say.\nSo then, Francesca—what did you think\nof your first Vernal Banquet?
It was SUPER fun! Thanks to you guys,\neveryone has a better idea of what the\nHalidom is all about.
...Plus, it's given me a look at how all\nthese folks feel about the place they\ncall home.
A hometown is more than just a place\nwhere you're from—it's a source of\npride, comfort, and spirit.
I recall those feelings from the days\nwhen I used to attend the Banquet.

And I as well. I thought I'd have nothing
to do with the Banquet once I lost my
own home, and yet find myself pleased
to have come here today.
If you like, Francesca, you could come\nagain next year as the official \nrepresentative of the Halidom.
You seem rather more excited about this\nthan I would have suspected.
Are you kidding me? Since everyone here\nuses barter instead of money, I'm loaded\nwith goods from villages far and wide.
I'm gonna sell, sell, sell until there's\ngold pouring outta my EARS!
Goodness, but you are a merchant to\nyour core! Still, I'm glad you had fun.
It was certainly a Banquet that represented\nwe people of the Halidom.
And I cannot wait for the next one!
